<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="jiechen — AI / Cloud / DevOps Engineer. 13 years building shipping software across AI agents, Cloudflare Workers, FastAPI, and LLM gateway infrastructure."
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		Hi, I'm <strong>jiechen</strong> (GitHub <a href="https://github.com/bbfans">@bbfans</a>), an
		<strong>AI / Cloud / DevOps Engineer</strong> with 13 years of hands-on software development
		experience. My work lives at the intersection of AI agent orchestration, edge cloud computing,
		and production-grade infrastructure automation.
	</p>

	<p>
		My core focus areas are <strong>AI Agent orchestration and protocol compatibility</strong> —
		working with MCP (Model Context Protocol), ACP, and subagent collaboration patterns to build
		composable, multi-agent systems. On the infrastructure side, I specialize in
		<strong>Cloudflare Workers</strong> full-stack deployments (Workers + KV + R2),
		<strong>FastAPI</strong> backend architectures, and <strong>Docker / Podman</strong>
		containerization. One of my ongoing projects is building an <strong>LLM API gateway / Bifrost</strong>
		that aggregates multiple LLM providers with automatic failover — a practical solution for
		running AI workloads reliably in production. I also work with <strong>GitHub Copilot
		subscription agent runtime</strong>, <strong>Playwright + browser automation</strong>,
		and maintain a <strong>TypeScript + Python</strong> dual-stack workflow.
	</p>

	<p>
		Here are six projects I'm actively maintaining right now:
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>1. bbfans-portal</strong> — This site. An Astro-based personal tech portal
		that doubles as my writing outlet and project index.<br />
		<strong>2. Hermes Agent</strong> — An AI agent orchestration CLI; currently the main
		project I'm iterating on for subagent coordination and tool calling pipelines.<br />
		<strong>3. copilot-agent-lite</strong> — A lightweight GitHub Copilot subscription agent
		runtime, keeping Copilot features available outside official client boundaries.<br />
		<strong>4. Kijiji Real-Time Monitor</strong> — A wheel-price monitoring bot for Kijiji
		that scrapes listings and pushes Telegram alerts on new matches.<br />
		<strong>5. blog.1001020.xyz</strong> — A minimal blogging engine built entirely on
		Cloudflare Workers, KV, and R2 — no origin server required.<br />
		<strong>6. Hermes Desktop</strong> — The web UI frontend for Hermes Agent, running on
		port <code>8787</code>, providing a graphical interface to the agent orchestration layer.
	</p>

	<p>
		On the community side, I've been active on GitHub as <strong>@bbfans</strong> for 13 years,
		with <strong>94 repositories</strong> spanning everything from dev tooling to infrastructure
		as code. My GitHub Pages portfolio is at
		<a href="https://bbfans.github.io">https://bbfans.github.io</a>.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Future directions:</strong> I'm particularly interested in pushing MCP and ACP
		protocol adoption further, making multi-agent systems easier to compose and debug. On the
		infrastructure side, I want to keep exploring edge-native architectures — Workers + R2 for
		static assets, KV for state, and zero-trust patterns for public-facing automation. I'm also
		exploring how GitHub Copilot's agent runtime can be extended with custom tools and
		subscription-based workflows. This blog is where I write about what I'm building and what
		I'm learning along the way.
	</p>
</Layout>
